# Dependencies — each sub-package (kg/, mcp-gemini-video/) installs its own
node_modules/

# Knowledge graph database — a binary that gets rewritten constantly (bad fit
# for git). It's your portable "talent-pool master": back it up / merge it with
# kg/scripts/merge-db.js rather than committing it. Delete these lines if you
# really do want the knowledge version-controlled here.
*.db-wal
*.db-shm

# Secrets — never commit the Gemini key (it lives in the GEMINI_API_KEY env var;
# .env.example stays as the template)
.env
**/.env

# Course material — for THIS course it's the cholf5《Claude Code in Action》中文版
# (a small, PUBLIC community translation: github.com/cholf5/claude-code-in-action).
# It's tiny text/HTML (~77KB), so we TRACK both the pristine clone (course/) and the
# generated chapter/lesson tree (Claude Code 實戰_課程講義/) — that way the cockpit's
# lesson catalog works straight after `git clone`, no manual download needed.
# (Images are hot-linked from the course's public S3 CDN, so no media lands here.)

# Lesson digests + rewritten web-notes (notes/) — INTENTIONALLY TRACKED so the
# re-read caches sync across machines (Windows ↔ MacBook). These contain verbatim
# copyrighted course slide text (gemini_digest_pdf OCR).
# ⚠️ This is ONLY acceptable because the repo is PRIVATE. If it is ever made
#    PUBLIC, re-add `notes/` to this file FIRST (copyright) before pushing.

# Safety net: never commit lecture media wherever it lands (any project layout)
*.mp4
*.mov
*.mkv
*.webm
*.srt

# Python bytecode (from the Whisper transcribe script)
__pycache__/
*.pyc

*.zip

# dual-plan rendered HTML — regenerated from plan.md by render.py; the .md is
# canonical and stays in git, the .html (and history/) is a local view.
plans/**/plan.html

# study-web runtime state (last lesson + chat history) — machine-local
study-web/state.json

kg/viewer/graph-data.json